OL,3,CWet February leads to plunge in
OL,4,Cshopping trips
OL,6,FShopping visits across the UK fell in
OL,7,FFebruary as wet weather kept consumers
OL,8,Fat home, figures show.
OL,10,FTotal UK footfall was down 4.7% year
OL,11,Fon year, a plunge from January's 0.6%
OL,12,Fdecrease, according to British Retail
OL,13,FConsortium (BRC)-Sensormatic data.
OL,15,FShopping centres saw a 5.5% fall while
OL,16,Fhigh street footfall was down 5.4%.
OL,18,FLondon was among the weaker
OL,19,Fperformers, recording its steepest
OL,20,Fdrop in footfall since April 2024.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/4
